How much advantage would there be to using and Orange Pi 5 over a Raspberry Pi 4? Anand’s Coprocessor Roundup is from last year, but I assume that it should still be mostly accurate. What I am more interested in knowing is how much of an advantage is there to be gained in real conditions? Also, would the NPU in the RK3588S be a step up or down from a coral?

The NPU is better than a Coral, but model performance will affect things more than the absolute differences in processors.

The Opi5 is still about 2x as powerful as an Rpi4. This difference is most notable when running 2 or more cameras that take advantage of the cores. Single core performance is still better too.

four:

2 different cameras that only run different pipelines

Parallel pipelines on the same coprocessor would be better served by the additional cores available on opi5.

It begs the question - why not have separate coprocessors for each camera and pipeline instead? Is there actually a benefit to only having one coprocessor board?
